	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 15th 2:18 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There is a school of thought in the EQ world that goes something like this:<br><br>Because Shadowknights are the next best tanks to Warriors (along with Paladins), they need to make sure they have the optimum number of hitpoints at the high end of the game.&nbsp;&nbsp;Stamina is therefore a vitally important statistic.  However, not all players will be able to get optimum gear and make Level 60.<br>The important thing to keep in mind when you assign your stats is the kind of equipment you believe you will have access to.  If you can get access to the really good items then go hard into stamina and the extra hitpoints will reward you when you finally reach Level 60.  This is primarily due to the changes in the way HP is calculated from level 50 - 60.<br><br>Therefore, one could argue to dump ALL BONUS POINTS IN STA, IF such person was a &quot;hardcore&quot; type player &amp; was determined to play much in the end game, REGARDLESS of race.  Yeah, playing an ORG or TRL early on might be a little frustrating, due to their lack of high INT, but, what many people struggle to accept, is that a SK/PLD is a TANK, supplemented by spells.  From lvl 50 onward, when you can get nice items, probably some that add INT, the extra HP will shine &amp; you wont be sorry.<br><br>Therefore, ask yourself what kind of player are you.  If hardcore, dump all into STA, regardless of race, otherwise, consider the weaknesses of each race &amp; dump accordingly.<br><br>As far as picking a ORG vs a TRL, see earlier message, save for the INT comment, which, could be different if you are a hardcore player.<br><br>They are both super races to pick if going to be an SK (some might argue they are the 2 best classes to choose from), so don't let anyone tell you otherwise.  The proof is in the numbers &amp;, in the endgame, all the best armor can be worn by any class.<br><br>Lunatic<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
